A new luxury villa development, better known as the Falcon Island Residential Project has just been launched by Al Hamra. The project is island-based will be developed with a total project cost of US$ 272M. It is also believed that the project is reaffirming the plans for the development of Al Hamra and the northern emirate. The project is set to take shape in the Al Hamra Village residential community. Read Also Agreement Signed for Development of 1st Methanol Production Facility in UAE The Falcon Island Residential Project will offer its residents an exclusive, vibrant and secure community that has been well designed for holiday trips, as well as the private living. The site can be accessed via both sea and land, and there are docking facilities available for yachts and boats as well as ample spaces for cars. Al Hamra expressed that they have always been focused on the investment and development in upscale lifestyle experiences and services and products that exceed expectations. The developer revealed that the Falcon Island Residential Project, which will be implemented in phases, is projected to be completed by the next 2 years from its launch. The north island will be unveiled as the project’s first phase which will consist of 240 villas that would range from one bedroom to seven ensuite bedrooms units. The villas will offer residents between 120 square meters and 650 square meters of living space. The villas will also be within well-landscaped green plots that reach up to 1,000 m2, with available options for private pools alongside exclusive beach access. CEO, Benoy Kurien, explained that the Falcon Island Residential Project aims to bring forth an extraordinary take on the everyday essential offering exclusivity in every possible way. The highlight of the project is that 70% of the island will be dedicated to open spaces.